JavaScript.content:
Understanding the most powerful array methods in JavaScript:

**Map** - Transform each element
```js
const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
const doubled = numbers.map(x => x * 2);
// Result: [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]
```

**Filter** - Select elements that match a condition
```js
const ages = [12, 18, 25, 30, 15];
const adults = ages.filter(age => age >= 18);
// Result: [18, 25, 30]
```

**Reduce** - Accumulate values
```js
const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
const sum = numbers.reduce((acc, curr) => acc + curr, 0);
// Result: 15
```

Modern asynchronous JavaScript patterns:

**Basic async/await**
```js
async function fetchUser(id) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${id}`);
    const data = await response.json();
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to fetch user:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}
```

**Parallel requests**
```js
const [users, posts, comments] = await Promise.all([
  fetch('/api/users').then(r => r.json()),
  fetch('/api/posts').then(r => r.json()),
  fetch('/api/comments').then(r => r.json())
]);
```

Remember: Always use try/catch for error handling!

Vue3.content:
Key concepts for Vue 3 Composition API:

**Setup function with ref and reactive**
```js
import { ref, reactive, computed } from 'vue';

export default {
  setup() {
    const count = ref(0);
    const user = reactive({
      name: 'John',
      age: 30
    });

    const doubleCount = computed(() => count.value * 2);

    function increment() {
      count.value++;
    }

    return { count, user, doubleCount, increment };
  }
};
```

**Using script setup (recommended)**
```vue
<script setup>
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';

const count = ref(0);
const doubleCount = computed(() => count.value * 2);

function increment() {
  count.value++;
}
</script>
```

Different ways to react to data changes in Vue 3:

**watch() - Watch specific reactive sources**
```js
import { ref, watch } from 'vue';

const question = ref('');
const answer = ref('');

watch(question, async (newQuestion, oldQuestion) => {
  if (newQuestion.includes('?')) {
    answer.value = 'Thinking...';
    const result = await fetchAnswer(newQuestion);
    answer.value = result;
  }
});
```

**watchEffect() - Auto-track dependencies**
```js
import { ref, watchEffect } from 'vue';

const todoId = ref(1);
const data = ref(null);

watchEffect(async () => {
  data.value = await fetch(`/api/todos/${todoId.value}`);
});
```

CSS.content:
Creating responsive layouts with CSS Grid:

**Basic Grid Template**
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
  padding: 2rem;
}
```

**Named Grid Areas**
```css
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    'header header header'
    'sidebar main main'
    'footer footer footer';
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

.header { grid-area: header; }
.sidebar { grid-area: sidebar; }
.main { grid-area: main; }
.footer { grid-area: footer; }
```

Astro.content:
Building components in Astro.js:

**Basic Astro Component**
```astro
---
// Component Script (runs at build time)
const title = 'Welcome to Astro';
const items = ['Fast', 'Flexible', 'Modern'];
---

<div class="card">
  <h2>{title}</h2>
  <ul>
    {items.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
  </ul>
</div>

<style>
  .card {
    padding: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }
</style>
```

**Using Framework Components**
```astro
---
import ReactCounter from '../components/Counter.jsx';
import VueCard from '../components/Card.vue';
---

<ReactCounter client:load />
<VueCard client:visible />
```
